Description: CVE-2026-56406 - Fix integer overflow in XML_ParseBuffer
 libexpat before 2.8.2 lacked an overflow check in XML_ParseBuffer that
 was present in XML_Parse. Copy the same check across so XML_ParseBuffer
 rejects oversized lengths instead of overflowing m_parseEndByteIndex.
 .
 The upstream fix uses the XML_INDEX_MAX macro (introduced in a later
 expat release). expat 2.2.10 does not define XML_INDEX_MAX, so this
 backport uses the same ((XML_Size)-1) / 2 idiom that XML_Parse already
 employs in this version for the equivalent overflow guard.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/99d8454fdf900a6d00c2a52748e6c0eeb507574d
Author: Sebastian Pipping <sebastian@pipping.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-24
---
--- a/expat/lib/xmlparse.c
+++ b/expat/lib/xmlparse.c
@@ -1902,6 +1902,14 @@
     parser->m_parsingStatus.parsing = XML_PARSING;
   }
 
+  /* Detect and avoid integer overflow */
+  if ((XML_Size)len > ((XML_Size)-1) / 2 - parser->m_parseEndByteIndex) {
+    parser->m_errorCode = XML_ERROR_NO_MEMORY;
+    parser->m_eventPtr = parser->m_eventEndPtr = NULL;
+    parser->m_processor = errorProcessor;
+    return XML_STATUS_ERROR;
+  }
+
   start = parser->m_bufferPtr;
   parser->m_positionPtr = start;
   parser->m_bufferEnd += len;
Description: Fix CVE-2026-56410 integer overflow in xmlwf resolveSystemId
 xmlwf in libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in
 resolveSystemId(): the length sum (tcslen(base) + tcslen(systemId) + 2)
 followed by multiplication by sizeof(XML_Char) can wrap, leading to an
 undersized malloc() and subsequent out-of-bounds writes.
 .
 This patch combines the two upstream commits (PR #1252, libexpat 2.8.2)
 that guard each operator in the length sum and protect the multiplication
 from integer overflow before allocation. The (XML_Char *) cast on malloc()
 used by the Debian 11 source tree is preserved. The first hunk adds
 <stdint.h> for SIZE_MAX (carried over from upstream commit
 deeb97f7c88d17a16b0ea2521a13733abc283347).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/deeb97f7c88d17a16b0ea2521a13733abc283347 and https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/cee20e91bf14dc7f6d2fc48f0d70d86b2dc3afea
Author: netliomax25-code <netliomax25@gmail.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-23

--- a/expat/xmlwf/xmlfile.c
+++ b/expat/xmlwf/xmlfile.c
@@ -32,6 +32,7 @@

 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <stdlib.h>
+#include <stdint.h> /* for SIZE_MAX */
 #include <stddef.h>
 #include <string.h>
 #include <fcntl.h>
@@ -125,8 +126,22 @@ resolveSystemId(const XML_Char *base, co
 #endif
   )
     return systemId;
-  *toFree = (XML_Char *)malloc((tcslen(base) + tcslen(systemId) + 2)
-                               * sizeof(XML_Char));
+
+  const size_t baseLen = tcslen(base);
+  const size_t systemIdLen = tcslen(systemId);
+
+  /* Detect and prevent integer overflow in the addition (without risking
+     underflow) */
+  if (baseLen > SIZE_MAX - systemIdLen || baseLen > SIZE_MAX - systemIdLen - 2)
+    return systemId;
+
+  const size_t charsRequired = baseLen + systemIdLen + 2;
+
+  /* Detect and prevent integer overflow in the multiplication */
+  if (charsRequired > SIZE_MAX / sizeof(XML_Char))
+    return systemId;
+
+  *toFree = (XML_Char *)malloc(charsRequired * sizeof(XML_Char));
   if (! *toFree)
     return systemId;
   tcscpy(*toFree, base);
Description: CVE-2026-56403 - Protect storeAtts and xcsdup from signed integer overflow
 Backport of upstream libexpat fixes for CVE-2026-56403 (CWE-190).
 .
 Debian's expat 2.2.10-2+deb11u7 already carries the CVE-2022-25313/25314/25315
 quilts, which add INT_MAX guards around the n+EXPAND_SPARE allocation and the
 (uriLen + prefixLen + i) sum in storeAtts().  This patch adds the protections
 that are still missing relative to upstream commit 12dc6d8d:
 .
   * Widen the prefixLen counting loop into size_t (candidateLen) and
     reject prefix names whose length would overflow int before narrowing.
   * Widen the localPart counting loop into size_t (localPartLen) and
     extend the existing INT_MAX accumulator check to include
     localPartLen > INT_MAX as well as the size_t-cast subtraction.
   * Add a SIZE_MAX/sizeof(XML_Char) guard before
     memcpy(uri, localPart, localPartLen * sizeof(XML_Char)) so the
     multiplication used for the copy size cannot wrap on platforms where
     sizeof(XML_Char) > 1.
 .
 In xcsdup() (xmlwf/xmlwf.c) the count and numBytes locals are widened from
 int to size_t, a SIZE_MAX/sizeof(XML_Char) guard is added before the
 multiplication used to size the malloc(), and <stdint.h> is added for
 SIZE_MAX.  This file is unchanged by Debian's existing quilt series.
 .
 No public API or ABI is changed.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/12dc6d8d3d65f79471a94d8565f6bf1cf245f648
 backport, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/147c8f36d6277d5c6011c098370a8362aed47b15
