 Description: Fix CVE-2026-56132 heap buffer overflow in doProlog scaffolding index store
 The scaffold backing array (dtd->scaffIndex) is reallocated using the
 caller parser's per-parser m_groupSize, but the DTD struct (which carries
 scaffIndex) is shared between a parent parser and any external
 parameter-entity sub-parser created via XML_ExternalEntityParserCreate().
 A sub-parser whose group nesting is shallower than the parent's can
 REALLOC the shared scaffIndex down to its own size; when the parent
 resumes and parses a deeper element content model, its bounds check
 passes (its private m_groupSize is still large enough), the doubling-grow
 path is skipped, and the next write lands past the shrunken buffer
 (CWE-821).
 .
 This backport squashes upstream commits 3a4eaf47 (Remove reuse of
 m_groupSize to count m_scaffIndex allocation), 58400483 (the primary
 fix that grows scaffIndex against its own tracked size before storing),
 and bca93b4b (remove the now-redundant scaffIndex expansion in the
 GROUP_OPEN path). Cosmetic commit 08baa7ef and the test commit
 353919b3 (basic_tests.c does not exist in 2.2.10) are intentionally
 omitted. A dedicated scaffIndexSize field is added to the DTD struct
 so the shared array's allocated size is tracked independently of any
 per-parser m_groupSize.
 .
 Hunk anchors are rebased so the patch applies cleanly on top of the
 prior CVE patches that os-patcher folds into the Debian quilt series
 (CVE-2024-8176, CVE-2026-24515, CVE-2026-25210, CVE-2026-32776,
 CVE-2026-32777, CVE-2026-32778, CVE-2026-45186, CVE-2026-50219,
 CVE-2026-56131) which together shift line numbers below the
 scaffolding region. The GROUP_OPEN hunk also now removes the full
 body of the redundant scaffIndex REALLOC block, including the
 integer-overflow guard that CVE-2026-32776 inserted inside it;
 an earlier revision of this backport only stripped the two REALLOC
 lines and left that guard behind, which failed to apply once
 CVE-2026-32776 was folded into the series ahead of this patch.
