Description: Fix CVE-2026-56411 integer overflow in xmlwf endDoctypeDecl
 xmlwf in libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in
 endDoctypeDecl via NOTATION declarations. Promote notationCount
 and the loop index to size_t, and add a SIZE_MAX/sizeof guard
 before the malloc() multiplication, mirroring the upstream fix.
 .
 Backported to expat 2.2.10: adapts to the target's early-return flow
 (no goto cleanUp); on overflow, free the notation list and return
 like the existing malloc-failure branch. The <stdint.h> include for
 SIZE_MAX is not added here since CVE-2026-56403 (earlier in the
 Debian bullseye quilt stack) already adds it to this file for the
 same reason.
 .
 Rebased against the Debian bullseye quilt stack, in particular
 CVE-2026-56403, so the hunk anchors line up with the post-stack
 xmlwf.c rather than pristine upstream 2.2.10.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/528a4e5017e1bd3b48b689fd0c131df940ae3ea5
