Description: Fix CVE-2026-56412 - guard XML_TOK_DATA_CHARS handler calls in doCdataSection()
 libexpat before 2.8.2 does not consider XML_TOK_DATA_CHARS in
 doCdataSection() and thus lacks handler call depth tracking for handler
 calls during policy violations, which can lead to a use-after-free.
 This is an incomplete-fix follow-up to CVE-2026-50219.
 .
 The upstream fix wraps the charDataHandler invocations in
 doCdataSection() with beforeHandler()/afterHandler() helpers that
 maintain a per-parser m_handlerCallDepth counter (introduced as part
 of the broader CVE-2026-50219 reentrancy infrastructure).
 .
 CVE-2026-50219 is folded into this same Debian bullseye quilt stack
 ahead of this patch and already backports that full m_handlerCallDepth
 reentrancy infrastructure, including the parser struct field and the
 beforeHandler()/afterHandler() helpers - it just never wraps the
 charDataHandler calls inside doCdataSection() itself, which is exactly
 the gap this CVE closes. This patch therefore reuses the existing
 per-parser beforeHandler()/afterHandler() helpers verbatim rather than
 introducing a second, file-scope-static implementation of the same
 pair; an earlier revision of this backport assumed the CVE-2026-50219
