 static int
Description: CVE-2026-56407 - cap entity textLen against signed integer overflow
 libexpat before 2.8.2 has an integer overflow in doProlog that is related
 to storeEntityValue and entity textLen.  When the entity value pool length
 exceeds INT_MAX, casting the size_t pool length to a signed int used for
 ENTITY.textLen wraps to a negative value.  This patch caps the entity
 textLen against signed integer overflow by returning XML_ERROR_NO_MEMORY
 when the pool length would not fit in a signed int.
 .
 Upstream commit 30c2fc1 adds this guard in two places: doProlog and
 storeSelfEntityValue.  Debian bullseye ships expat 2.2.10, which has no
 storeSelfEntityValue helper (entity textLen is assigned only from doProlog),
 so only the doProlog hunk is backported here.
 .
 The xmlparse.c hunk is rediffed against the bullseye tree after the
 earlier queued CVE patches have already been applied, so context line
 numbers differ from a pristine 2.2.10 tree.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/commit/30c2fc179ce5d2b1b1bae30bbe0dfddeac894e13
Bug: https://github.com/libexpat/libexpat/pull/1262
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/1140557
Author: Sebastian Pipping <sebastian@pipping.org>
Applied-Upstream: 2.8.2
Last-Update: 2026-07-14
---
--- a/expat/lib/xmlparse.c
+++ b/expat/lib/xmlparse.c
@@ -4669,6 +4669,10 @@
         enum XML_Error result = storeEntityValue(
             parser, enc, s + enc->minBytesPerChar, next - enc->minBytesPerChar);
         if (parser->m_declEntity) {
+          /* Detect and prevent signed integer overflow */
+          if ((size_t)poolLength(&dtd->entityValuePool) > (size_t)INT_MAX) {
+            return XML_ERROR_NO_MEMORY;
+          }
           parser->m_declEntity->textPtr = poolStart(&dtd->entityValuePool);
           parser->m_declEntity->textLen
               = (int)(poolLength(&dtd->entityValuePool));
